Ad Text:
Anduril Industries is a defense technology company with a mission to transform U.S. and allied military capabilities with advanced technology. By bringing the expertise, technology, and business model of the 21st century’s most innovative companies to the defense industry, Anduril is changing how military systems are designed, built and sold. Anduril’s family of systems is powered by Lattice OS, an AI-powered operating system that turns thousands of data streams into a realtime, 3D command and control center. As the world enters an era of strategic competition, Anduril is committed to bringing cutting-edge autonomy, AI, computer vision, sensor fusion, and networking technology to the military in months, not years.

ABOUT THE TEAM
The Analytics team is responsible for modeling our internal data into reusable entities that generalize how Anduril operates. From those entities we build workflows, dashboards, and metrics that drive better and faster decision-making. You will work with stakeholders from across the company to understand how Anduril functions and model our data to create the digital twin of our operations.

ABOUT THE JOB
We’re looking for people who love ontologies - defining domains and writing the code that puts those models into action. Ideally you are passionate about the next generation of defense technology and love building efficient and understandable data models. You prioritize velocity and are interested in pushing the frontiers of what analytics can do within an organization - think data applications rather than just dashboards.

This role presents an exciting opportunity to be part of our team’s expansion into Australia. As the first team member in Australia, you'll be able to shape the role and team, directly influencing the work and direction of where it goes.

WHAT YOU'LL DO

Lead the building of Anduril’s ontology for Australia across a number of domains such as Finance, Supply Chain, Manufacturing, People, and Sustainment
Collaborate with stakeholders, collecting requirements, and writing the code that results in Secure, Timely, Accurate, Trusted, and Extensible Data Models
Seek out problems that can be solved with data and proactively work with the organization to make it a reality
Become a trusted resource for Anduril leadership in helping them run their organizations more effectively
REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS

5+ years of experience in an analytics focused role - Analytics Engineer, Data Engineer or Analyst / Consultant with a strong engineering background
You are motivated by our mission. We are working to solve the biggest problems in defence
Your weekend reading usually involves authors named Kimball or Inmon or modern data modeling blogs
You’re energized by business impact & a self-starter: you’d rather build an imperfect data model quickly that is used by many people than a perfect data model that collects dust
You thrive in cross-functional projects that have a heavy combination of technical requirements and user-focused workflows
Expert with SQL and experience with Python or other programming languages
Experience with data stack tools: dbt, Redshift, Looker/Tableau, Palantir Foundry
You are empathetic: you are eager to see the world from your users’ perspective
Ability to obtain and maintain an Australian Government Security Clearance (NV2).

Anduril is an equal-opportunity employer, and we encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply. If you are someone passionate to work on problems that matter, we’d love to hear from you!

The salary range for this role is an estimate based on a wide range of compensation factors, inclusive of base salary only. Actual salary offer may vary based on (but not limited to) work experience, education and/or training, critical skills, and/or business considerations. Highly competitive equity grants are included in the majority of full time offers; and are considered part of Anduril's total compensation package. Additionally, Anduril offers top-tier benefits for full-time employees, including: 

Healthcare Benefits 

US Roles: Comprehensive medical, dental, and vision plans at little to no cost to you. 
UK & AUS Roles: We cover full cost of medical insurance premiums for you and your dependents. 
IE Roles: We offer an annual contribution toward your private health insurance for you and your dependents. 

Additional Benefits 

Income Protection: Anduril covers life and disability insurance for all employees. 
Generous time off: Highly competitive PTO plans with a holiday hiatus in December. Caregiver & Wellness Leave is available to care for family members, bond with a new baby, or address your own medical needs. 
Family Planning & Parenting Support: Coverage for fertility treatments (e.g., IVF, preservation), adoption, and gestational carriers, along with resources to support you and your partner from planning to parenting. 
Mental Health Resources: Access free mental health resources 24/7, including therapy and life coaching. Additional work-life services, such as legal and financial support, are also available. 
Professional Development: Annual reimbursement for professional development 
Commuter Benefits: Company-funded commuter benefits based on your region. 
Relocation Assistance: Available depending on role eligibility. 

Retirement Savings Plan 

US Roles: Traditional 401(k), Roth, and after-tax (mega backdoor Roth) options. 
UK & IE Roles: Pension plan with employer match. 
AUS Roles: Superannuation plan. 

The recruiter assigned to this role can share more information about the specific compensation and benefit details associated with this role during the hiring process. 

To view Anduril's candidate data privacy policy, please visit https://anduril.com/applicant-privacy-notice/.

Salary: Salaried position with great perks and benefits
Ad Text:
The Arnott's Group portfolio of brands continues the 160-year legacy of the Arnott family, providing quality, great-tasting food to create delicious moments for consumers across the world.

At The Arnott's Group, you'll join a diverse, values-driven team passionate about delivering quality products like Tim Tams, Shapes, V8 juice and more—plus enjoy them too!

We are proud of our legacy, but we aren't stopping here! Collaborators, innovators, and agile thinkers with a curious mind thrive here. Be part of a future which is full of delicious moments created locally, by you!

About the Role:

Reporting to the Head of Commercial Finance, the FP&A Manager is a key member of the ANZ Finance team, responsible for driving financial planning, reporting and strategic insights across the ANZ Snacking business. This role takes ownership of forecasting, budgeting and analysis, delivering data-driven recommendations that influence business strategy to accelerate growth. It offers a unique opportunity to operate in a high-performing, proactive environment where your contributions have a visible impact.

Operating as a central function within Commercial Finance, the ANZ FP&A team is responsible for reporting, consolidating, and analysing the performance of the ANZ region. The team provides strategic insights and recommendations to senior leadership and prepares leadership-level performance presentations. It also leads the financial forecasting and budgeting processes, ensuring data accuracy and clarity on performance drivers.

Success in this role demands exceptional analytical capability, strong commercial acumen and the ability to influence stakeholders in a dynamic, fast-paced FMCG environment. Acting as a trusted advisor, the FP&A Manager provides the actionable insights that enables the business to optimize profitability and deliver sustainable long-term growth.

What your days look like:

Business partnering
Partner with Sales, Marketing and Supply Chain Finance to provide clarity, confidence and integrity in financial reporting
Shape the financial outlook by distilling complex data into clear, compelling insights that inform strategy and enable proactive decision-making
Tracking and delivering insights into performance v targets;
Working with the senior leadership team, providing value add analytics to influence business decisions.

Financial reporting & planning
Drive the budgeting cycle, uplift forecasting capability, enhance financial reporting, and provide commercial insights that influence strategic and operational decision-making;
Lead the annual budgeting and 5-year strategic planning process with clear governance;
Develop and execute robust scenario planning and financial modeling to evaluate potential outcomes, enabling proactive strategies and informed decision-making under uncertainty.

Process Improvement:
Lead continuous improvement initiatives to streamline the planning cycle, reducing complexity and enhancing efficiency/effectiveness through automation and best practices;
Design and implement standardized forecasting and reporting processes to improve accuracy, consistency, and timeliness across the organization with clear ownership and accountabilities;
Embedding improved ways of working to support the overall IBP /Commercial planning cycle.

Leadership:
Coach and mentor direct reports (2) to build capability and cultivate a high-performance culture rooted in continuous improvement and accountability;
Proactively identify and create learning opportunities that strengthen team expertise, engagement and future-readiness, ensuring adaptability in a dynamic business environment.

The Ingredients for Success:

Just like you can't make a Tim Tam without chocolate, there are a few essential ingredients we need for this role;

CA/CPA/CIMA qualified with demonstrated FP&A commercial finance experience
Proven experience in the FMCG sector, with an understanding of the industry dynamics and commercial drivers
Exceptional stakeholder management capabilities with the confidence to challenge and influence
Strong commercial acumen with the ability to translate financial data into actionable business insights
Advanced financial modelling, forecasting and analytical capabilities
Proactive, solutions-focused mindset with a hands-on approach in a fast-paced environment
Excellent communication skills, capable of presenting complex information clearly and persuasively

Perks:

Discounted Gym Memberships
12 Weeks Paid Parental Leave for all new parents.
Free onsite parking
Discounted Products
Discounted Health Insurance
NAWO membership

Our Culture:

We stand for high performance with integrity and find moments of pride and celebrate the wins gained from our collective effort. These are part of our culture and the cornerstones of The Arnott's way. When you join our team, you can expect to experience a real sense of belonging, be empowered with accountability, be recognised for your contribution, collaborate with great people.

To Apply:

If this sounds like your next opportunity, please follow the link, and apply.

We value diversity in our workforce. If you require any reasonable adjustments, please inform our team so that we can work together to support your needs throughout the recruitment process.

*We do not accept unsolicited resumes from agencies

Job Title: Data Analyst / Engineer, Databricks, DBT, SQL, Brisbane
Ad Text:
Data Analyst (Migration Projects)

Location: Brisbane CBD / Hybrid

About the Role

We are looking for a Data Analyst who loves the challenge of migration projects. You will play a pivotal role in translating complex data into actionable insights and migrating data from one core system to another, as well as reconciliation work.

Tech Stack:-

To be successful in this role, you should have hands-on experience with:

SQL: Expert level for complex querying and data manipulation.

dbt: Experience in modular data modelling and documentation.

Build insightful dashboards and reports to support business decision-making.

Perform deep-dive analysis to ensure data integrity during and after the migration process.

This is a role that will need to be filled in the next week with ideal start date in February.

For further information please send your details to ram.basra@randstaddigital.com.au and I will be in touch ASAP.

Senior Portfolio Analyst - Telco

6-Month Contract

$800 - $950 a day (inclusive)

Melbourne CBD (Hybrid)

About the Organisation

Talenza is partnering with a leading telecommunications organisation delivering complex, regulated portfolios across customer, billing, and revenue-critical domains. With a strong focus on customer outcomes, billing accuracy, credit performance, and risk management, this organisation operates in a highly visible and compliance-driven environment.

About the Role

As a Senior Portfolio Analyst, you will provide portfolio-level oversight and actionable insights across customer and billing initiatives, with a strong emphasis on compliance, risk, and credit performance. You will analyse delivery, financial, and operational data to support informed decision-making across executive and senior leadership forums.

This role works closely with Risk, Sales, Service, Product, Engineering, Marketing, and Customer teams, sitting at the intersection of commercial performance, customer experience, and regulatory obligations.

Key Responsibilities

Deliver end-to-end portfolio reporting across customer, billing, and credit initiatives

Provide actionable insights on portfolio health, compliance, risk exposure, and delivery performance

Report on billing and credit key performance indicators including accuracy, leakage, debt, remediation, and customer impact

Analyse portfolio exposure across customer outcomes, billing integrity, credit risk, and regulatory obligations

Track and report on financial performance including budgets, forecasts, and benefits realisation

Support portfolio planning, prioritisation, and investment decision-making

Identify cross-initiative dependencies and their impact on customer, revenue, and risk outcomes

Partner closely with Risk, Sales, Service, Product, Engineering, Marketing, and Customer teams to align insights and actions

Prepare executive-ready dashboards, insights, and SteerCo reporting

Maintain data quality and integrity across portfolio tools, KPI dashboards, and reporting packs

Key Selection Criteria

Proven experience as a Senior Portfolio Analyst / PMO Analyst in large, complex environments

Telecommunications experience strongly preferred, particularly across customer, billing, and credit domains

Strong understanding of billing, credit performance, compliance, and risk management

Demonstrated experience reporting on operational and financial KPIs at portfolio level

Advanced reporting and data analysis capability (Excel, Power BI, portfolio tools)

Ability to produce clear, concise executive insights and recommendations

Strong stakeholder engagement across Risk, Sales, Service, Product, Engineering, Marketing, and Customer teams

Benefits

$800 -$950 per day inclusive

6-month contract with extension potential

High-profile role within a regulated telco environment

Melbourne CBD location with hybrid working

About The Role
Kinetic IT is looking for an experienced Corporate Planning & Performance Management Specialist to drive enterprise-wide planning, forecasting, performance measurement and strategic insight across a complex IT services organisation.
This is a specialist role, focused on end-to-end business planning and analysis, working closely with the Strategic finance team, CEO, CFO and senior leaders to shape both short-term execution and long-term strategy.

Responsibilities will include:

• Lead monthly, quarterly, and annual financial planning and forecasting, including revenue, billing, resourcing, utilisation and profitability drivers
• Develop and maintain integrated financial models (3-way P&L, balance sheet, cash flow), pipelines, scenario analysis, and ROI assessments to support strategic decisions
• Deliver performance reporting, dashboards and executive summaries for Board, Executive and Leadership teams, translating complex data into actionable insights
• Act as a trusted business partner, ensuring leaders trust the numbers, understand performance drivers, and can make informed decisions
• Support business cases and investment decisions, including modelling options, assessing ROI, and scenario planning
• Track and evaluate performance-based incentive programs, linking achievement to strategic objectives and recommending improvements to drive desired outcomes
• Contribute to valuation, benchmarking, and operating model optimisation, leveraging best practices from other organisations
• Lift the maturity of planning, forecasting, and performance management processes, implementing tools, templates, and methodologies that increase accuracy and efficiency
• Partner across business units to identify opportunities for improvement, ensuring plans reflect operational realities and strategic priorities

What you’ll bring to the table:
• Proven track record as a Corporate Financial Planning Specialist for a services industry type company, ideally enterprise scale.
• Agile mindset & Systems thinker – Ability to approach complex organisational challenges with flexibility, adaptability, and a structured, holistic perspective across processes and teams.
• Strong Excel modelling skills
• Advanced Power BI skills
• Collaborative skills –having worked effectively with finance teams, business units, and senior leaders to drive alignment and achieve shared goals.
• Financial storytelling skills – Skilled at translating complex financial data into concise, actionable narratives that influence decision-making and strategy.
• Planning and performance management systems skills – Hands-on experience with enterprise planning, forecasting, and reporting systems to drive accuracy, efficiency, and insight.
• Working with C-level executives – Comfortable collaborating with senior leaders, providing strategic insight and guiding business planning and performance discussions and board reporting.
• Large, complex financial modelling – Ability to design and interpret detailed financial models for enterprise-level planning, forecasting, and valuation.
• In-depth business model and planning knowledge
• Microsoft Dynamics and Workday Adaptive Planning (or similar systems) – Proficiency in ERP and planning platforms, leveraging technology to improve planning, forecasting, and reporting processes.
• Master’s in Commerce/Finance/CA/CPA or similar

Kinetic IT is a leading Australian IT services provider specialising in Intelligent Workplace, Cloud, Cyber Security, Digital Infrastructure and IT Service Management. We are unlocking the potential of technology to enrich lives of Australian communities.

Senior Portfolio Analyst - Performance Analytics
 
A leading Australian organisation is seeking an experienced Senior Portfolio Analyst to join a high-performing Performance Analytics team within a complex consumer and financial services environment.
 
This is a high-impact role where data, risk, and customer experience intersect. You will play a critical part in shaping advanced analytics and reporting solutions across identity verification, billing, credit, and compliance processes, with exposure to senior leaders across Finance, Risk, Product, Technology, and Customer teams.
 
The Opportunity
 
Reporting to a senior analytics leader, you will directly influence business outcomes by delivering actionable insights, building robust data assets, and developing enterprise-level reporting frameworks. Your work will support operational efficiency, fraud prevention, regulatory compliance, and improved customer experiences across the full customer identity lifecycle.
This role offers strong visibility, autonomy, and the opportunity to work on complex, enterprise-scale data initiatives.
 
Key Responsibilities

Lead the design and delivery of advanced analytics, dashboards, and automated reporting solutions
Develop data assets and monitoring frameworks to support identity verification, authentication, billing, and credit controls
Translate policies and regulatory requirements into practical reporting and business rules
Deliver high-quality, actionable insights to senior stakeholders to drive performance and risk outcomes
Partner closely with business teams to understand requirements and manage analytics deliverables
Ensure data accuracy, governance, and alignment with enterprise reporting standards
Contribute to data modelling across warehouse, analytical, and semantic layers
 
About You
 
You are a senior analytics professional who enjoys working at the intersection of data, risk, and business performance. You are confident engaging with senior stakeholders and translating complex analysis into clear, commercial insights.
 
You will bring:

5+ years' experience in data analytics, reporting, or performance analytics
Advanced SQL skills and experience working with large, complex datasets
Strong experience with BI and analytics tools (e.g. Tableau, Cognos, Alteryx or similar)
Advanced Excel skills (including automation and data integration)
Experience in data modelling, data governance, and reporting frameworks
Background in credit risk, financial services, telecommunications, or a regulated environment (highly regarded)
Strong communication and presentation skills, with the ability to influence senior stakeholders
Interested?
Please apply via the link or email a copy of your resume to dwood@launchrecruitment.com.au

Bravas is the specialist shared services supporting Hunter Premium Funding and Arteva Funding. We provide deep expertise across Finance, Compliance, IT Transformation, HR and Marketing that allows our brands to focus on delivering market-leading premium funding solutions.

We are seeking a Head of Data & AI to lead our data and AI transformation initiatives. This pivotal role will shape the architecture, engineering, and automation strategies that power scalable, secure, and ethical AI solutions across the Group.

As specialists in premium funding, data is at the heart of everything we do. We are seeking a leader who can design robust data architectures, build high-performing engineering teams, and implement AI automation to enhance operational efficiency and customer experience, while ensuring compliance and safety at scale.

About the Role

Reporting to the Chief Transformation Officer, you will lead a high-calibre team to transform our organisation into a data-driven and AI-enabled enterprise. You will bridge the gap between complex engineering and commercial value, elevating data as our strategic asset and driving scalable, safe, and resilient data and AI platforms that are fully compliant with global standards.

Key Responsibilities

Data Strategy & Governance

Define and execute a comprehensive data strategy aligned with business objectives, driving measurable ROI through data monetisation and fostering a data-driven culture.

Establish strong data governance frameworks to ensure data quality, integrity, privacy, security, and compliance.

Manage stakeholder groups across business units to maintain data governance standards and stewardship.

Architecture & Engineering Leadership

Design and oversee modern, enterprise-grade data and AI platforms to support advanced analytics and AI workloads.

Lead the development of full-stack AI applications to optimise processes and deliver measurable business outcomes, ensuring compliance with responsible AI practices and regulatory requirements.

Continuously evolve the data and AI platform architecture, evaluating 'buy vs. build' and integration trade-offs to ensure platforms remain composable, modular, portable, and cost-optimal.

AI Innovation & Organisational Learning

Embed AI capabilities into core business operations and workflows to achieve sustainable business outcomes and transform the organisation into an AI-enabled workforce.

Lead the development of ethical and responsible AI standards, policies, and guidelines, ensuring models are rigorously designed and tested for hallucinations, bias, and adversarial attacks before deployment.

Drive organisational AI learning and development programs to bridge the skills gap, working with HR to redefine job roles and workflows in an AI-augmented environment.

Establish and lead a governance framework compliant with APRA CPS 230 and CPS 234, ensuring operational resilience of AI models and upholding transparency requirements for Automated Decision-Making (ADM) under the reformed Australian Privacy Act.

Team Leadership & Collaboration

Build and mentor a high-performing team of data engineers, architects, and AI specialists.

Collaborate with and empower cross-functional stakeholders to continuously enhance and innovate data and AI initiatives.

Act as a trusted advisor to the Board and C-suite, translating complex technical data and AI concepts into clear business risks and opportunities

What We’re Looking For

Proven experience in data architecture, engineering, and delivery, preferably within a financial institution or similar industry.

Familiarity with the Australian regulatory landscape (APRA, SIC, OAIC), including experience operationalising CPS 230 (Operational Risk) and CPS 234 (Information Security).

In-depth knowledge of AI/ML model integration, with experience in frameworks such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, AutoGen, LangChain, and n8n.

Experience with AIOps workflows and pipelines, from initiation and training to production deployment, including full observability, model evaluation, and monitoring.

Hands-on experience with cloud data and AI platforms (e.g., AWS SageMaker, Azure Fabric).

Strong background in data governance, security, and compliance frameworks.

Ability to scale AI solutions safely and responsibly across complex environments using Responsible AI frameworks.

Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills.

This is a great opportunity to join Bravas and lead the data evolution across our group, shaping how we harness AI to drive smarter business decisions.

If you enjoy the intersection of people, process, and technology and want to make a genuine impact on our future growth, we encourage you to apply

Job Title: Head of Financial Planning and Analysis
Ad Text:
About Us: 
  
At Ubank, we empower the digital generation to achieve financial success. Think of us as your daily money companion, offering a unified view of your finances with smart features and real-time insights. Save more, track spending, and achieve home ownership faster with Ubank.  
  
The Why: 

Your purpose is to deliver robust, timely and insightful financial plans/forecasts, business performance reporting and analysis. You love data and getting into the detail, as well as stepping back to deliver clear, concise, actionable insights to business partners.   

  
Key Responsibilities:

Financial Planning & Forecasting


Collaborate with executives to define business strategy and key performance measures.
Source and challenge business assumptions to drive accurate financial forecasts, budgets, and planning models.
Develop and maintain robust financial planning models aligned with business needs.
Manage the end-to-end financial planning process, including development, review, approval, and reporting.
Balance strong business partnering with independent financial control—challenging the business to achieve ambitious yet realistic outcomes.
Business Performance, Reporting & Partnering

Build and maintain effective relationships with business partners.
Deliver tailored performance reporting to stakeholders including the Board, Executive Team, and Managers—covering both financial and non-financial metrics.
Support executive accountability through timely, data-driven reporting.
Identify performance issues, risks, and opportunities, providing actionable recommendations.
Collaborate with Group Financial Control, Treasury, and Investor Relations to ensure accurate inputs for reporting.
Partner with Financial Accounting and BI teams to meet business needs and maintain management account hierarchies.
Understand internal cost allocation methodologies and provide strategies to manage costs effectively.
Analysis & Data Visualisation

Conduct regular and ad-hoc analysis to deliver insights for informed decision-making—covering pricing models, customer analysis, competitor benchmarking, and activity-based costing.
Present analysis in a clear, compelling format to influence stakeholders.
Work with BI technologies to design, develop, and maintain reporting and insight tools.
Collaborate with IT to ensure trusted data sources and optimise reporting processes for clarity and impact.
Leadership & Management

Lead, coach, and develop direct reports (currently one) to ensure high performance and engagement.
Contribute actively as part of the Finance leadership team.
Your Experience
Minimum 10 years in accounting, finance, or FP&A (retail banking preferred).
At least 5 years’ experience managing people.
Strong accounting expertise combined with commercial acumen.
Excellent knowledge of risk analysis, budgeting, and forecasting.
Advanced proficiency in financial software and MS Office.
Experience with advanced tools such as Power BI, TM1, Tableau.
Skilled in using BI tools to automate reporting and create dashboards.
Highly analytical with strong mathematical aptitude.
Exceptional communication, influencing, and relationship-building skills.
Proven problem-solving ability and attention to detail.
Strong organisational and leadership capabilities.
Degree in Accounting, Finance, Economics, or related field.
Experience in digital or banking environments.
Exposure to greenfield, start-up, or high-growth organisations.
Understanding of structured file/database formats (CSV, XML, XBRL).
Knowledge of SQL.

Why Ubank?

You will work closely with departments across the Bank to strengthen operational risk management, provide independent oversight and assist with risk assessments, reporting, control reviews, and stakeholder coordination. You will also contribute to the development of frameworks and tools that support continuity of operations and effective third-party risk management


Key Responsibilities


Support the development and implementation of the Bank's operational risk and resilience frameworks.
Provide Line 2 oversight of risk and control assessments, including business continuity, incident response, and third-party risk.
Support the preparation of risk reports, dashboards, and governance materials.
Maintain and update risk registers, control libraries, and action plans.
Help coordinate responses to internal audits, regulatory reviews, and assurance activities.
Monitor key risk indicators (KRIs) and emerging risk trends.
Collaborate with Line 1 stakeholders to embed operational risk management.
Contribute to continuous improvement of risk processes, templates, and tools.



About you


7+ years' experience in operational risk, business continuity or a related discipline, ideally within financial services or a regulatory environment.
Strong understanding of risk management frameworks (e.g. ISO 31000) and regulatory expectations (e.g. CPS 220, CPS 234, CPS 230).
Experience working in or with large, complex organisations undergoing risk transformation is advantageous.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to translate risks into business impacts.
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to influence and collaborate across functions.
Familiarity with GRC tools and risk reporting platforms is advantageous.
Relevant tertiary qualifications in risk, finance, economics, compliance, or a related discipline



About the team


Reporting to the Senior Manager, Operational Risk and Resilience within the Risk Management and Compliance team (Line 2), you will play a leading role in establishing effective Line 2 review, challenge, and insight across the Bank's material risk classes. Establishing strategic and trusted relationships across the Bank is fundamental to the team's success.

Data Governance Specialist | Queensland Government Sector

Are you a data governance expert with a talent for establishing frameworks and embedding best practices within complex environments? We are seeking a seasoned Data Governance Specialist for a critical engagement within a prominent Queensland Government entity.

The Opportunity

Operating within the insurance arm of the state government, this role is pivotal in establishing formal data ownership and governance across the entire organisation. Leveraging an existing framework, you will be responsible for developing comprehensive policies, onboarding key data roles, and ensuring rigorous compliance across all datasets.


This is a contract position running from 2 March until 30 June 2026, based full-time onsite at a premier Brisbane CBD location.


Key Deliverables

As the Data Governance Specialist, your primary focus will be to:

Develop and formalise a bespoke data governance policy and associated procedures specifically tailored to the organisation's needs.

Onboard and train key data governance roles, including Data Stewards and Data Custodians.

Ensure compliance with high-level data standards, focusing specifically on data quality, data lineage, and data integrity across all systems.

Produce documentation and training materials to support the long-term adoption of governance policies.

Collaborate closely with technical data professionals and business stakeholders to embed governance principles into daily operations.

About You

To be successful in this role, you will demonstrate:

Proven Experience: A strong track record in developing and implementing data governance frameworks, policies, and procedures.

Technical Knowledge: A deep understanding of data quality, lineage, and integrity principles.

Stakeholder Engagement: Exceptional communication skills with the ability to bridge the gap between technical teams and non-technical business stakeholders.

Training Capability: Experience in onboarding and mentoring roles such as Data Stewards and Custodians.

Industry Background: Previous experience working within the insurance sector or a similarly highly regulated environment.




Highly Regarded Skills:

Familiarity with Medallion Architecture (Raw, Standardised, Consumer layers).

Knowledge of Azure Databricks or equivalent cloud data platforms.

About us 

At CitiPower and Powercor and United Energy, we’re proud to deliver electricity to 2 million Victorian customers every day through our network of poles and wires. But more than that, we’re here to power communities, support local businesses and keep critical services running smoothly, we’re essential to them all – and none of this happens without our people. About the role 

This role leads the research, development, deployment, and continuous enhancement of advanced Computer Vision, Perception AI, and Spatial Intelligence capabilities to improve operational efficiency, asset intelligence, safety, and automation across the electrical distribution network. Working with high-dimensional multi-modal data—including imagery, video, spatial datasets, and selected LiDAR/3D applications—the role delivers core perception technologies that enable a variety of digital and hardware initiatives. It is also responsible for establishing robust MLOps practices to ensure scalable model development, reliable deployment, ongoing monitoring, and continuous improvement. The role works collaboratively with other specialised teams across the organisation to ensure alignment, clear boundaries, and efficient integration of related capabilities. 

Key responsibilities 

Lead, coach, and develop a specialised team of computer vision, perception AI, and spatial AI engineers to deliver high-quality outcomes.

Create and maintain the Perception & Spatial AI Capability Roadmap, ensuring alignment with organisational priorities and complementary teams.

Own the full lifecycle of vision and perception models, including data management, training, validation, deployment, monitoring, and continuous improvement.

Implement scalable MLOps pipelines for data ingestion, model versioning, CI/CD for ML, retraining, and operational monitoring.

Lead the design and development of advanced computer vision and perception AI models for detection, segmentation, anomaly identification, change detection, and scene understanding.

Build scalable perception algorithms using imagery, video, 3D spatial data, and multi-sensor inputs to support operational decision-making.

Collaborate with the Generative AI (agentic applications) team on multi-modal solutions where perception outputs integrate with LLMs, agents, or decision systems.

Employ generative AI techniques—such as synthetic data, diffusion models, or multi-modal fusion—to strengthen perception model performance. 

For more information on the role’s responsibilities, please click here to download the position description.

7+ years in AI/ML roles with strong computer vision or perception experience.

Deep expertise in computer vision and perception AI.

Prior leadership of AI/ML teams is strongly preferred.

Experience in utilities, energy, infrastructure, robotics, or other asset-intensive industries is advantageous.

Proficiency in Python, PyTorch/TensorFlow, and GPU-accelerated computing.

Knowledge of imagery, video, spatial modelling, and selective LiDAR use cases.

Tertiary qualification in computer science, ML/AI, engineering, robotics, or a related field.

Job Title: Senior Technical Business Analyst - Data & Analytics (Supply Chain)
Ad Text:
The Senior Technical Business Analyst – Data & Analytics partners with Supply Chain stakeholders to define business problems, assess current data and reporting ecosystems, and shape future-state analytics capabilities using modern cloud data platforms and emerging AI technologies.

This role combines strong business analysis, data discovery, and stakeholder engagement skills with a forward-looking mindset, focusing on how advanced analytics, automation, and AI can enhance decision-making and operational performance. The role suits someone comfortable working with ambiguity and helping establish new ways of working in an evolving analytics and AI-enabled environment.

Key Responsibilities
Lead discovery to understand Supply Chain data flows, ingestion, lineage, and transformation across cloud data platforms (e.g. Snowflake, Databricks, or equivalent).
Assess current BI and reporting environments (e.g. Power BI, Tableau), identifying gaps, risks, and opportunities to enable advanced analytics and AI-driven insights.
Partner with senior stakeholders to define business problems, ideate data, analytics, and AI use cases, and improve operational efficiency and productivity.
Facilitate workshops and interviews to gather and document business, functional, and non-functional requirements, including data governance, privacy, and security considerations.
Define current-state and future-state processes and translate requirements into epics, user stories, and acceptance criteria.
Contribute to data, analytics, and AI strategy by providing structured analysis and clear recommendations aligned to business outcomes.
Skills & Experience
Proven experience as a Senior or Technical Business Analyst delivering data, analytics, or AI-enabled initiatives.
Strong experience with modern cloud data platforms (Snowflake, Databricks, or AWS/Azure/GCP equivalents).
Hands-on experience with BI tools such as Power BI and/or Tableau.
Strong stakeholder engagement skills, including facilitation with senior business leaders.
Experience in Supply Chain or Manufacturing environments is highly desirable.
Demonstrated interest in emerging AI technologies, including exploratory use cases, proofs-of-concept, or applied analytics.
This is a day-rate contract opportunity, and the hiring manager is seeking the right team member to join as soon as possible.
